# 2024-10-02 13:58:48.163690
+Okay here's some context of how some project I'm working on creates new stream nodes.  And I would like you to take this information and apply it for our Aurene Python script.  So yeah, you can only extract the relevant information but make sure that this works.  Because before I had to put in my GitHub username which shows me that there was some remote  still registered or something like that.  So I don't have to do that when I create a new repository using this codebase.  So please replicate this part of the codebase or like this approach that the codebase embodies  for our purposes here. Based on the provided code, the creation of new DreamNodes is handled by the create-new-node IPC handler. Here's how it works and the equivalent terminal commands you can use to replicate this 
+process:                                                                                                                                                                                         
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+ 1 The handler first checks if a template repository called "DreamNode" exists in the DreamVault.                                                                                                
+ 2 It then clones this template repository to create the new DreamNode.                                                                                                                          
+ 3 After cloning, it removes the origin remote to disconnect from the template.                                                                                                                  
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+Here are the equivalent terminal commands to replicate this process:                                                                                                                             
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+ # Assuming you're in the DreamVault directory                                                                                                                                                   
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+ # 1. Check if the template exists (this is done implicitly in the code)                                                                                                                         
+ ls DreamNode                                                                                                                                                                                    
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+ # 2. Clone the template to create a new DreamNode                                                                                                                                               
+ git clone DreamNode NewNodeName                                                                                                                                                                 
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+ # 3. Remove the origin remote                                                                                                                                                                   
+ cd NewNodeName                                                                                                                                                                                  
+ git remote remove origin                                                                                                                                                                        
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+In the actual code, these operations are performed using Node.js's fs module and the child_process.execSync function. Here's the relevant part of the code:                                      
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+ // Clone the template repository                                                                                                                                                                
+ const { execSync } = require('child_process');                                                                                                                                                  
+ execSync(`git clone "${templatePath}" "${newNodePath}"`, { stdio: 'inherit' });                                                                                                                 
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+ // Remove the origin remote to disconnect from the template                                                                                                                                     
+ execSync('git remote remove origin', { cwd: newNodePath });                                                                                                                                     
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+To replicate this elsewhere, you would need to:                                                                                                                                                  
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+ 1 Have a template repository named "DreamNode" in your DreamVault directory.                                                                                                                    
+ 2 Use the git clone command to create a new repository based on this template.                                                                                                                  
+ 3 Remove the origin remote from the newly created repository.                                                                                                                                   
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+Remember to replace "NewNodeName" with the actual name you want to give to your new DreamNode. Also, ensure you're in the correct directory (your DreamVault equivalent) when running these      
+commands.                                                                                                                                                                                        
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+                                                                                                                                                                                                 
+Tokens: 12k sent, 387 received.                                                                                                                                                                  
+Cost: $0.04 message, $0.04 session. Use --no-stream for accurate caching costs.                                                                                                                  
+─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+public/ipcHandlers.js                                                                                                                                                                            
+>  

