# 2024-10-02 14:56:06.288753
+Certainly! The "run aider" handler uses the following terminal commands:                                                                    
+                                                                                                                                            
+                                                                                                                                            
+ const aiderProcess = spawn('osascript', ['-e', `                                                                                           
+   tell application "Terminal"                                                                                                              
+     do script "cd '${repoPath}' && codad && aider"                                                                                         
+     activate                                                                                                                               
+   end tell                                                                                                                                 
+ `]);                                                                                                                                       
+                                                                                                                                            
+                                                                                                                                            
+Let's break this down:                                                                                                                      
+                                                                                                                                            
+ 1 The handler uses the spawn function from Node.js's child_process module to execute an AppleScript command.                               
+ 2 The AppleScript command does the following:                                                                                              
+    • It tells the Terminal application to: a. Open a new Terminal window b. Execute the following commands in that window:                 
+       • cd '${repoPath}': Change the directory to the repository's path                                                                    
+       • codad: This appears to be a custom command or alias (it's not a standard Unix command)                                             
+       • aider: Run the Aider tool c. Activate the Terminal window (bring it to the foreground)                                             
+                                                                                                                                            
+So, in essence, it's running these commands in a new Terminal window:                                                                       
+                                                                                                                                            
+                                                                                                                                            
+ cd '/path/to/your/repo'                                                                                                                    
+ codad                                                                                                                                      
+ aider                                                                                                                                      
+                                                                                                                                            
+                                                                                                                                            
+The codad command is not a standard command, so it's likely a custom alias or script that's part of your development environment. It's      
+executed before running aider, possibly to set up some environment or activate a virtual environment.                                       
+                                                                                                                                            
+The aider command is then run, which starts the Aider tool in the context of your repository.     Okay, so here's some context of how I have currently approached this in an app I'm building,  where I can basically select a repository and run the runadr command and it will successfully  open a terminal window, so I can immediately start with the project.  Can you please create a new Python script that executes these terminal commands and  basically takes in as an argument...  Now basically, can you please expand the dreamnode_creator.py file so it not only creates the new Dreamnode  but rather also goes into that directory, like, you know, runs this code and basically  immediately spawns a new Ada session.  That would be cool.

